# All of these are stdlib CVEs found in usr/local/bin/gosu inside the
# itzg/minecraft-server image (confirmed via `trivy image --format json`,
# PkgPath usr/local/bin/gosu). gosu (https://github.com/tianon/gosu) is a
# single-purpose setuid/setgid-then-exec helper the image's entrypoint uses
# to drop from root to UID 1000 - per its own docs, once it execs the target
# process "gosu itself is no longer resident or involved... at all", and it
# never makes network connections, handles TLS, or parses untrusted network
# input. The vulnerable crypto/tls stdlib code is present only because Go
# statically links the full stdlib - it is never actually invoked here.
#
# Re-verify this reasoning still holds before renewing past the expiry - if
# gosu's role in the image ever changes, or a newer image build ships a
# patched gosu, drop these entries instead.
